         <listPerson>
            <person xml:id="pers1995">
               <p>Originally of <placeName>Yorkshire</placeName>, Taylor came to know <persName><ref
                        target="/persons/pers0215.xml"/>Mary Bosanquet</persName> in <date
                     when="1767">1767</date>, while in <placeName>London</placeName> trying to
                  resolve some debts. In <date when="1768-06">June 1768</date> he helped persuade
                        <persName><ref target="/persons/pers0215.xml"/>Bosanquet</persName> and her
                  circle of friends to move to the <placeName>Leeds</placeName> area and located the
                  Cross Hall farm which she purchased. Taylor and his family moved next door to
                  Cross Hall and he supervised <persName><ref target="/persons/pers0215.xml"
                     />Bosanquet</persName>&apos;s farm. This proved a poor choice, as Taylor was a
                  poor manager and soon in further financial trouble. Taylor also did some local
                  preaching during this time.</p>
            </person>
         </listPerson>
